properties.headline: Flood Warning issued January 11 at 9:39AM CST until January 13 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Lincoln IL
properties.description:
...The National Weather Service in Lincoln IL has issued a flood
warning for the following river in Illinois...

Mackinaw River near Congerville affecting McLean...Tazewell and
Woodford Counties

.The following forecasts are based on observed precipitation, soil
moisture conditions, and forecast precipitation.

The National Weather Service in Lincoln IL has issued a

* Flood Warning for
The Mackinaw River near Congerville.
* From Sunday morning until Monday evening.
* At  845 AM Saturday the stage was 6.2 feet.
* Flood stage is 13.0 feet.
* Moderate flooding is forecast.
* Forecast...Rise above flood stage by tomorrow morning and continue
to rise to near 14.0 feet by tomorrow evening.The river will fall
below flood stage by Monday afternoon.
* Impact...At 13.0 feet...Widespread agricultural flooding occurs.
properties.instruction:
Persons with interests along this river need to prepare for flooding.
Stay tuned for further updates on this flooding situation.
